σij are the Lennard-Jones diameter and well depth parameter which are obtained according to Lorentz-Berthelot mixing rules, σij = (σi + σj)/2 and ϵLJ = (ϵiϵj)1/2. Since the pore (carbon) atoms carry no charge, the nanotube-Stockmayer molecule interaction can be described by the short range term of U(rij). Here, both short-range repulsive and attractive dispersion interactions contribute to the solute-solvent interactions. In the next part of MD simulations, the short range interactions between pore atoms and solvent molecules are treated by the repulsive part of the Lennard-Jones potential as per the decomposition scheme of Weeks-Chandler-Andersen (WCA)59

