C. Rotational dynamics

Rotational motion of Stockmayer molecules can be analyzed by means of the angular velocity autocorrelation function Cω(t) and self-dipole moment correlation function Cµ(t). If ω(t) is the angular velocity of a solvent molecule at time t, then

